<BlogLayout
  title="How to Have the Perfect Santorini Dream Wedding"
  description="Everything you need to know to plan your perfect wedding in Santorini — from venues and timing to beauty and styling."
  date="June 23, 2021"
  category="Wedding Planning"
  image="/images/portfolio/santorini-bridal-looks-3.jpg"
>
  <p class="text-lg text-grey leading-relaxed">
    Santorini is one of the most sought-after wedding destinations in the world, and for good reason. With its breathtaking caldera views, iconic blue-domed churches, and golden sunsets, it provides an unmatched backdrop for your special day.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-display-sm font-serif italic text-charcoal mt-12 mb-4">Choosing the Right Season</h2>
  <p class="text-base text-grey leading-relaxed">
    The wedding season in Santorini typically runs from May through October. June and September offer the perfect balance of warm weather, fewer crowds, and stunning light. July and August are the peak months — the sunsets are spectacular, but you'll want to book well in advance.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-display-sm font-serif italic text-charcoal mt-12 mb-4">Finding Your Venue</h2>
  <p class="text-base text-grey leading-relaxed">
    From clifftop terraces in Oia to intimate vineyard settings in Pyrgos, Santorini offers venues for every style. Consider the time of day for your ceremony — a sunset ceremony at a west-facing venue creates unforgettable golden-hour photographs.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-display-sm font-serif italic text-charcoal mt-12 mb-4">Your Wedding Day Beauty</h2>
  <p class="text-base text-grey leading-relaxed">
    The Santorini climate — warm, dry, and breezy — requires special consideration for your makeup and hair. Long-lasting, humidity-resistant formulas are essential. Book a local expert who understands the island's unique conditions and can work with the natural light and setting.
  </p>
  <p class="text-base text-grey leading-relaxed mt-4">
    A trial session before the wedding day is invaluable. It gives you peace of mind and ensures your look is perfected well before the ceremony. Consider scheduling your trial at the same time of day as your wedding to see how the makeup and styling look in similar lighting conditions.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-display-sm font-serif italic text-charcoal mt-12 mb-4">Making It Unforgettable</h2>
  <p class="text-base text-grey leading-relaxed">
    The key to a perfect Santorini wedding is working with experienced local professionals who know the island intimately. From your photographer to your beauty artist, local expertise makes the difference between a beautiful wedding and an extraordinary one.
  </p>
</BlogLayout>
